Sure looks like it. This may indicate a flaw in our testing strategy. We
have K profiles for the K runners we have, and they work fine with proper
transitive dependency resolution when used individually. Precommit,
however, we simply turn on all the profiles and hope that enabling them all
concurrently just works. (Which it mostly, sorta, has.)

Motivation is: BQ tests are failing on DirectPipelineRunner due to testing of pickling/unpickling.

We should not be picking unpickling native sink objects since they might contain unpicklable data (proto objects in this case).
